{"collectionID": ["MOdels for Data Analysis and Learning - MODAL"], "accessibility": [], "topic": [{"term": "Statistics and probability", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/topic_2269"}, {"term": "Gene expression", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/topic_0203"}, {"term": "DNA polymorphism", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/topic_2885"}], "owner": "ELIXIR-FR", "cost": null, "relation": [], "download": [], "validated": 1, "publication": [{"doi": "10.1186/s12859-014-0394-y", "note": null, "version": null, "pmid": null, "type": "Primary", "pmcid": null, "metadata": {"title": "MPAgenomics: An R package for multi-patient analysis of genomic markers", "abstract": "\u00a9 Grimonprez et al.; licensee BioMed Central Ltd.Background: Last generations of Single Nucleotide Polymorphism (SNP) arrays allow to study copy-number variations in addition to genotyping measures. Results:, standing for multi-patient analysis (MPA) of genomic markers, is an R-package devoted to: (i) efficient segmentation and (ii) selection of genomic markers from multi-patient copy number and SNP data profiles. It provides wrappers from commonly used packages to streamline their repeated (sometimes difficult) manipulation, offering an easy-to-use pipeline for beginners in R. Conclusions: provides an easy tool to analyze data from SNP arrays in R. The R-package is available on CRAN.", "citationCount": 1, "authors": [{"name": "Grimonprez Q."}, {"name": "Celisse A."}, {"name": "Blanck S."}, {"name": "Cheok M."}, {"name": "Figeac M."}, {"name": "Marot G."}], "date": "2014-12-14T00:00:00Z", "journal": "BMC Bioinformatics"}}], "homepage_status": 0, "credit": [{"typeRole": ["Provider"], "name": "IFB ELIXIR-FR", "url": null, "gridid": null, "note": null, "orcidid": null, "typeEntity": "Institute", "email": null}, {"typeRole": ["Primary contact"], "name": "Samuel Blanck", "url": null, "gridid": null, "note": null, "orcidid": null, "typeEntity": "Person", "email": "samuel.blanck@inria.fr"}], "biotoolsCURIE": "biotools:mpagenomics", "elixirPlatform": [], "elixirNode": [], "version": ["1"], "elixir_badge": 0, "homepage": "http://modal.lille.inria.fr/wikimodal/", "function": [{"note": "Data normalization is a preprocessing step that consists in a correction of biological and technical biaises due to the experiment. It is only available for Affymetrix arrays.", "input": [{"data": {"term": "Raw microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3110"}, "format": []}], "operation": [{"term": "Gene expression analysis", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_2495"}], "cmd": null, "output": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}]}, {"note": "This function segments the previously normalized profiles and labels segments found in the copy-number profiles.", "input": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}], "operation": [{"term": "Nucleic acid feature detection", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_0415"}, {"term": "Microarray probe design", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_0309"}], "cmd": null, "output": [{"data": {"term": "Experiment report", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_2531"}, "format": []}]}, {"note": "This function segments allele B fraction extracted from the previously normalized data. This tools works only on normal-tumor study.", "input": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}], "operation": [{"term": "Gene expression analysis", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_2495"}], "cmd": null, "output": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}]}, {"note": "This function filters obtained by the segmentation and calling tool.", "input": [{"data": {"term": "Experiment report", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_2531"}, "format": []}], "operation": [{"term": "Sequence feature comparison", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_0256"}], "cmd": null, "output": [{"data": {"term": "Experiment report", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_2531"}, "format": []}]}, {"note": "This function selects some relevant markers according to a response using penalized regression.", "input": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}], "operation": [{"term": "Annotation", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_0226"}], "cmd": null, "output": [{"data": {"term": "Sequence tag profile", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_2535"}, "format": []}]}, {"note": "This function extracts the copy number profile from the normalized data.", "input": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}], "operation": [{"term": "Gene set testing", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_3224"}], "cmd": null, "output": [{"data": {"term": "Sequence features", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_1255"}, "format": []}]}, {"note": "This function segments normalized profiles provided by the user and labels segments found int he copy-number profiles.", "input": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}], "operation": [{"term": "Gene expression analysis", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/operation_2495"}], "cmd": null, "output": [{"data": {"term": "Processed microarray data", "uri": "http://edamontology.org/data_3111"}, "format": []}]}], "lastUpdate": "2018-12-10T12:58:50Z", "otherID": [], "description": "A package for multi-patients analysis of genomic markers. It is devoted to (i) efficient segmentation and (ii) genomic marker selection from multi-patient copy number and SNP data profiles.", "toolType": ["Workbench"], "editPermission": {"type": "private", "authors": []}, "language": [], "link": [{"url": "http://modal.lille.inria.fr/wikimodal/", "note": null, "type": "Software catalogue"}], "biotoolsID": "m